div4.p:
The novel was widely reviewed in Critical Review 60 (Sept 1785): 233-34
(the young author “is by no means deficient in many of the requisites which should occupy her task”); 
English Review, 6 (1785): 232 (“In the execution it is not altogether defective . . . and few
of the present run of novels deserve so much praise”); §European Magazine 8 (1785): 394;
§Monthly Review 73 (1785): 392; and Town and Country Magazine 17 (Nov
1785): 658 (“above the common run of novels”).
